5 A BILL
6 TO BE ENTITLED
7 AN ACT
8
9 Relating to crimes; to prohibit the disclosure or
10 transmission of certain images of deceased individuals taken
11 as part of a coroner or law enforcement investigation; and to
12 provide criminal penalties for a violation.
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
14 Section 1. (a) Any photograph or image of a deceased
15 individual or human remains that is taken as part of a coroner
16 death investigation or law enforcement investigation,
17 regardless of whether the investigation is active or not, and
18 regardless of whether the photograph or image was taken by use
19 of a personal electronic device or device belonging to a state
20 or local agency, is prohibited from being disclosed,
21 transmitted, or used for any purpose other than an official
22 coroner or law enforcement purpose or as otherwise authorized
23 by law or civil proceedings.
24 (b)(1) Any person who violates subsection (a) is guilty
25 of a Class B misdemeanor.
26 (2) Any person who, for a consideration or other gain,
27 including money, goods, or services, discloses or transmits
28 any photograph or image described in subsection (a) is guilty
